consensus text: magnificence and order of the external
world must have called up that emotion
which is described by a modern poet as
A sense sublime of something far more
Where dwelling in the light of setting Suns
And the round ocean and the living Air
And the blue sky, and in the Mind of man
A motion and a spirit that impels
All thinking things all objects of all though[superscript]t[/superscript]
